data.title: Warsaw Public Library, Warsaw
data.meta_description: Warsaw Public Library was established in the year 1907. The library society was born out of the efforts of the region's noted educators including Ludwik Krzywicki and Stanisław Leszczyński. It remains one of the most important libraries in the capital and also one of the country's largest libraries. It is home to more than 1,380,000 editions of manuscripts, magazines, books and other published material.
